I"Û<p>If you force-quit any Microsoft Office application on macOS using Option-Command-Esc, this annoying and useless error reporter
launches:</p>

<p><img src="/assets/mer.png" alt="" /></p>

<p>The Microsoft Error Reporting app exists within <em>each</em> Office app installed on your Mac, i.e. within Word, OneNote,
PowerPoint, etc.</p>

<p>This is insane, so letâ€™s remove it.</p>

<p>Open terminal and type in the following to delete:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>sudo rm -rf /Applications/Microsoft\ *.app/Contents/SharedSupport/Microsoft\ Error\ Reporting.app/
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>This will go through <code class="highlighter-rouge">/Microsoft\ Excel.app</code>, <code class="highlighter-rouge">/Microsoft\ PowerPoint.app</code>, etc. and delete the app.</p>

<p>Be extremely careful using <code class="highlighter-rouge">sudo</code> and <code class="highlighter-rouge">rm</code>. Donâ€™t wreck your system.</p>
